Lanys T'Vyl</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulistero001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Listero001</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/1/01 1:20:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most important stats for monks and why?</span><hr size=1> hp/ac most important, and stam.  Str maybe secondary to that.<br>
/shrug <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucelesteawildrose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celestea Wildrose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/1/01 8:19:27 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://kayleechen.homestead.com/files/bouncie2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most important stats for monks and why?</span><hr size=1> stam and strength are the two most important ones. 20 stam at 60 is 80hp.. 20 str is about 2 to 2.5% increase in damage overall...<br>
 <p><br>
<img src="http://kayleechen.homestead.com/files/celesteasignature.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulistero001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Listero001</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/1/01 8:45:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most important stats for monks and why?</span><hr size=1> Don't agree with you on that one celestia, at 60 ac/hp far more important than stam/str.  Because there are many stat boosts on items stam gets maxed on raids fairly quickly from buffs, and at level 60 you'll probably be spending most of your time raiding.  So stam starts to lose its value, although you should take it if you need it.  Same goes for str, but more, you can easily max out str with buffs at level 60, without purposely trying to get str, it isn't worth it.  Hp/ac however are always needed stats.(some say one more than the other, but /shrug)<br>
/shrug <br>
(For those that don't know stats effectively stop having effect after 255) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulistero001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Listero001</A> at: 6/1/01 8:45:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucelesteawildrose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celestea Wildrose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/2/01 9:37:02 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://kayleechen.homestead.com/files/bouncie2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most important stats for monks and why?</span><hr size=1> Sorry, I was just talking about the free points at character inception... I don't go for + stat items much myself. AC/hp and a little stamina to make sure I'm over 100 or if it just happens to be on something that is fairly good overall.<br>
I wear a Sode of Empowerment because I'm proud of having gotten it, and its very good imo. All my other stat boosts are incidental though.<br>
 <p><br>
<img src="http://kayleechen.homestead.com/files/celesteasignature.jpg" border="0"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucelesteawildrose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celestea Wildrose</A> at: 6/2/01 9:38:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uhsianlichen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hsian Li Chen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><FONT COLOR=AA0000><B>Lanys.com Moderator</B></FONT></span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/2/01 9:40:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most important stats for monks and why?</span><hr size=1> ya know what though?  I started Xian with:<br>
<br>
10 str<br>
5 agi<br>
5 dex<br>
5 cha (i think, it's been a while)<br>
<br>
and it don't make a hoot of difference.  Put them in whatever, it really doesn't matter... were i to do it again i think i'd put it all in Agi, cuz str and sta are so easy to buff, and agi adds ac /shrug<br>
<br>
honestly, just make the character... the assignment points at the beginning are really a drop in the bucket ;D<br>
<br>
