<hr width=400>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulistero001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Listero001</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/15/01 3:48:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most important stats for monks and why?</span><hr size=1> Would have to say in the end stats don't really matter that much.  Str maxes out fast, and once you hit level 60 you'll be raiding most of the time with shaman buffs.  Same with stam really.  I'm not saying to avoid str/stam items/points.  I'm just saying that in the long run it really doesn't matter that much.  Just go with the high ac/hp stuff, take stam if you need it, resists are nice.<br>
/shrug <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utrukoflanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trukoflanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/16/01 9:27:31 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://falcor81.future.easyspace.com/face.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most important stats for monks and why?</span><hr size=1> put all points into stam its the hardest stat to max<br>
need 205sta unbuffed to hit max with buffs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubiten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Biten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/28/01 6:53:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most important stats for monks and why?</span><hr size=1> New monk here...<br>
I have 103str, 141agi(305ac), 119dex at 11th lvl 289hp, can solo reds (14-15 mobs). I think AGI/STR would be most important. Though I've not played another monk with a different main stat...could be wrong. /shrug<br>
<br>
STR=Kill slightly quicker.<br>
AGI=Live longer.<br>
<br>
I guess ? <br>
As much of both as possible <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulistero001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Listero001</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/28/01 12:44:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most important stats for monks and why?</span><hr size=1> No, str does not matter in the long run, and maxes out relatively quickly, it has very little effect on actual damage.  Agil is nice for a bit of ac, but going full out on ac/stam/hp items before checking agil is always a good idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaguer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laguer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/14/01 3:04:25 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.austin.rr.com/fendryl/sumo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most important stats for monks and why?</span><hr size=1> I did STR and AGI split equally at the beginning.  Works for me, but truly they're right.  It doesn't seem to matter as long as you don't max your wis or int hehe.  Heck even AC doesn't matter as much to me since I wear a TON of resist gear when pulling due to the stupid casters nuking me to death grrr.  Though when pulling warrior types I have to say if you ain't got no SoW you gotta get the AC/HP gear back out /sigh <p>Laguer Bloodreaper  <BR>  
